# Obsolete string, do not remove
;Using three distinct interactive graphic representations — Graph, Clock and List — Lightbeam enables you to examine individual third parties over time and space, identify where they connect to your online activity and provides ways for you to engage with this unique view of the Web.
Lightbeam kitatekiujtia eyi tataman taixkopimej ten mouikaj se uan okse —Taixkopin gráfico, Tepostonaltamachiualoni uan Tajkuilolamat kampa taman tekpantokej — uan kinkauilia oksekin kiitaskej itech tiempo uan espacio, kiixmatiskej kampa monamiktiaj initekiuj itech Internet uan kinmaka tataman kemej kikuiskej nejin tachiyalis tein amo okse ijkuitik onkak.


;The default Graph view provides a real time visualization of every site you visit and all third party requests made from your browser.
Tachialis Gráfico tein yekinika kiixtalijkej kitemaka keniuj se uelis kiitas itech tonal tein yekmelauj sejsemej sitios tein se kikalpanos uan nochi tajtanilis tein teaxka tein mochiua itech se inavegador.


;The Graph view also provides adjustable filters that allow you to visualize more types of data at a glance.
Tachialis Gráfico no kitemaka tatsetseloloni tein se uelis kipatas uan kikauilia se kiijsiujkaitas tataman datos.


;The List view provides more options for drilling down into individual sites.
Tachialis Tajkuilolamat kampa taman tekpantokej kitemaka okachi taman tatemolis taijtik sejsemej sitios.


;Site preferences in the List view enable you to block sites from connecting to your Firefox browser, watch sites you’re interested in or hide sites you don’t want to see visualized.
Kemej tikonteluelitas sitio itech tachialis Tajkuilolamat kampa taman tepantokej mistonkauilis tikontsakuas sitios tein monamiktiaj monavegador Firefox, uan tikonitas sitios tein mitsonyoltilanaj uan tikontatis sitios tein nion tikonnekis tikonitas.


;Lightbeam also offers an information panel that provides additional details about the site you selected and the sites it has connected to.
Lightbeam no mitsonmaka se taixnextiloni tein kitematiltia oksekin taman tein ika okachi tionmomachtis sitio tein tikonixpejpenak uan oksekin sitios tein achto tikinonnajnamiktij.


;The origins of Lightbeam
Kampa ualeujtok Lightbeam.


;Lightbeam began in July 2011 as Collusion, a personal project by Mozilla software developer <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.
Lightbeam peuak metsti julio 2011 kemej Collusion, se talnamikilis tein kichiuak akin kichijchiuak software Mozilla<a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.


;Inspired by the book, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul created an experimental add-on to visualize browsing behavior and data collection on the Web.
Kitamachilismakak amaix <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul kichiuak se tamajsikayot tein moneki kiyejyekoskej uan kualtia se kiitas keniuj monejnemiltiaj tatemolismej uan no se nesentililis datos itech Web.


;In February 2012, Gary Kovacs, Mozilla CEO at the time, introduced the Collusion add-on in a <a href="%s">TED talk</a> (now one of the most watched TED talks of all time) about exposing online tracking.
Itech metsti febrero 2012, Gary Kovacs, ijkuakon CEO tein kiixyekanaya Mozilla, kitenextilij tamajsikayot Collusion itech se <a href="%s">nechikolis TED</a> (axkan xa yejua nechikolis TED tein okachi kiitanij) uan kichiuak kinextij keniuj tetoktiliaj itech Internet.


;In September 2012, Mozilla joined forces with faculty and student researchers at <a href="%s">Emily Carr University of Art + Design</a> to develop and implement visualizations for the add-on.
Itech metsti septiembre 2012 Mozilla sentekitik iniuan akin momachtijtokej itech <a href="%s">Ueyikalnemachtiloyan Emily Carr tein Tayektsinchiualis uan Tachijchiualis</a> uan ijkon kisenchiujkej uan kitekitiltijkej tachialismej tein pouij nejin tamajsikayot.


;With the support of the Ford Foundation and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion has been re-imagined as Lightbeam and was launched in the fall of 2013.
Ika inepaleuil nechikol Ford Foundation uan Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion kiyekchijchiujkej kemej Lightbeam uan kitematiltijkej takoseui 2013.


