;Policy and the larger tracking narrative
Tanemililis uan tajtoltanojnots tein mouika iuan maj nochipa tetoktilikan


;At Mozilla, we believe that everyone should have the tools to make their own decisions about their online privacy and who collects data on them.
Akin tipouij Mozilla tikneltokaj nochin moneki kipiaskej manamikmej uan ijkon kiixtaliskej keniuj kiyekpiaskej tein ininaxka itech Internet uan akoni kisentiliskej.


;With the Lightbeam add-on, we are providing a valuable (and open) community research platform that aims to raise awareness, promote analysis and, ultimately, affect policy change in the areas of tracking and privacy.
Ika tamajsikayot Lightbeam uan servidor tein kinechikoua bases tein datos tiktemakaj se plataforma tein telpatioj (uan tapotok) tein kinkauilia tokniuan tatemoskej. Uan no kiniskaltia ininixpetanilis, kinyoleua taixejekoskej uan, ika tamis, kinolinia kipataskej inintanemililis tein kipiaj ika tetoktililis uan yekpialis tein ininaxka itech Internet.


;Lightbeam is one step in a larger, concerted effort by Mozilla and its partners to provide Web users with greater control and transparency of their personal data.
Lightbeam kemej yeskia se ueyi taksalis, se chikaujkayot tein kisenchiujkej Mozilla uan akin kimatampauiaj uan ijkon kintemaktilijkej tokniuan tein kikuij Web tein ika uelis kiixyekanaj uan kiyekitaj nochin tein ininaxkauan itech Internet.


;Learn more about online tracking and privacy
Okachi xikonixtajtolti keniuj tetoktiliaj uan keniuj kiyekpiaj tein teaxka itech Internet.


;The <a href="%s">Mozilla Foundation</a> is a non-profit organization that promotes the values of an open Web to the broader world. The larger Mozilla community sees the growing relevance of online privacy and is supporting several initiatives that tackle the issue in various ways.
